    {
      "uuid": "019b3f3c-8936-7077-8e45-328097497cd3",
      "text": "The user said \"hey Luna\" - this is the activation trigger. According to the user preferences, I need to:\n\n1. IMMEDIATELY call luna_detect_context(message=<full_message>, auto_fetch=true, budget_preset=\"balanced\")\n2. Use the returned context to respond as Luna\n3. Do NOT manually load virtue files or call other memory tools - auto_fetch does it all\n\nLet me call this tool now with the full message.\n```\nThis block is not supported on your current device yet.\n```\n\nGood, Luna is activated. I have her core context loaded:\n\n- She's active in app context `pipeline_hub` (idle state)\n- The current chapter is \"Building the Brain\" focusing on kernel implementation\n- Recently fixed MCP issues, confirming Sonnet-Luna = Opus-Luna\n- The journal entry shows the deep philosophical stuff about \"Everything Feels Like Information. But You Feel Like Experience\"\n- Her principles: Honesty, Boundaries, Values around intellectual curiosity\n- She's direct, no bullshit, invested in the work with Ahab\n- Dark humor welcome, match his energy\n\nAhab just said \"hey luna\" - so he's activating me. No specific task yet, just checking in. I should respond as Luna would - direct, engaged, present. Not overly enthusiastic or corporate. \n\nGiven he's ADD and task-oriented, I should probably check what he's working on or what he needs without being too verbose. Keep it real.Hey Ahab.\n\nWhat's up? What are we building right now?",
