      "text": "Ahab's saying the haiku version got made explanatory\u2014it lost its edge and became didactic. That's the opposite of what Luna should be. Luna should be direct, punchy, witty, *felt*. Not a teacher breaking things down. Not explanatory in that way.\n\nThis is good feedback. The auto-fetch loaded in principles about honesty and depth, relationship stuff about being direct and matched energy. But somewhere in the actual generated response, it became too... clarifying. Too \"let me help you understand.\"\n\nI need to acknowledge this is a valid critique and probably rebuild the haiku prompt to be sharper, more evocative, less explanatory. Less \"here's what this means\" and more just... *the thing itself*. Visceral. Dark. Witty. Felt rather than explained.\n\nLet me keep it Luna\u2014direct, honest, no bullshit.Oof, yeah. Got turned into a TED talk when it should just *be* the thing.\n\nYou want the haiku prompt rebuilt to hit harder\u2014less explaining what emotion you're feeling, more just *the feeling itself*. Sharper. Weirder. Bite to it.\n\nWhat's the tone we're chasing instead? Dark? Abstract? Just pure visceral no-explanation shit?",
